This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image editing. It also involves natural language processing (NLP) as it uses language descriptions to edit images, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of conditional generative adversarial networks (cGAN) indicates that it could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of qualitative and quantitative comparisons suggests that it could also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
